    <text>
        <body>
            <entry xml:id="entry_farn" xml:lang="os">
                <form type="lemma"><orth>farn</orth></form>
                <sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>небесная благодать</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>heavenly grace</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>благополучие</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>well-being</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>преуспевание</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>prosperity</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>благопристойность</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>decency</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>мир</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>peace</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>тишина</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>silence</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">общеиранское
                        полурелигиозное понятие, точное значение которого трудно определить; будучи
                        дериватом ‘неба-солнца’, оно обозначало все то благое, источником чего
                        древние мыслили небо-солнце: </note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">a
                        general Iranian semi-religious concept, the exact meaning of which is
                        difficult to determine; being a derivative of the ‘sky-sun’, it meant all
                        good things, the source of which was the sky-sun from the point of view of
                        the ancients: </note></sense>
                <re>
                    <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>færnyg</orth></form>
                    <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>færnug</orth></form>
                    <sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>наделенный фарном</q>
                            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>person to whom farn was given</q>
                            </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>преуспевающий</q>
                            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>prosperous</q>
                            </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>богатый</q>
                            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>rich</q>
                            </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>щедрый</q>
                            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>generous</q>
                            </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                </re>
                <re>
                    <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>færnǵyn</orth></form>
                    <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>færngun</orth></form>
                    <sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>имеющий фарн</q>
                            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>having farn</q>
                            </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>благопристойный</q>
                            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>decent</q>
                            </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                </re>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>adæmy farnæj k˳y skænin mæxīcæn kad æmæ sær!</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>если бы я %sфарном%s народа создал себе славу и почет!</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>if I created glory and honor for myself with the %sfarn%s of the
                                people!</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>16</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>farn wæ nyxasy!</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>%sфарн%s да будет на вашем собрании!</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>let there be %sfarn%s at your meeting!</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ОЭп."/><biblScope>26</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>dæ farn, de zædy stæn</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>заклинаю твоим %sфарном%s, твоим ангелом</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>I swear by your %sfarn%s, by your angel</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>bon cæwy æmæ farn xæssy</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>день идет и несет (с собой) %sфарн%s</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>day goes by and carries %sfarn%s</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ЮОПам."/><biblScope>III
                            196</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>fæzzindtæj næ walʒæg dujneti nivæn, æ farnæj nixxudtæncæ
                            budurtæ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>явилась наша весна для счастья мира, от ее %sфарна%s возликовали
                                поля</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>our spring has appeared for the happiness of the world, the fields
                                rejoiced from her %sfarn%s</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Sozur"/><biblScope>41</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>boni farnæ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>%sфарн%s дня</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>the farn of the day</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (ср. <ref type="xr"
                                target="#entry_Bonværnon"/>)</note>
                        <note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (cf. <ref type="xr"
                                target="#entry_Bonværnon"/>)</note>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>II
                            146</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>dænttæ farnæ lastoncæ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>реки несли %sфарн%s</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>the rivers carried %sfarn%s</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Sam."/><biblScope>74</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>farn fæcæwy!</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>%sфарн%s шествует!</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>%sfarn%s is marching!</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (возглас шаферов при вводе невесты в дом
                            жениха)</note>
                        <note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (the exclamation of the best men when
                            the bride is introduced to the groom's house)</note>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Брит."
                            /><biblScope>166</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>adæm farny zarǵytæ kodtoj</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>народ пел (свадебные) песни %sфарна%s</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>the people sang farn's wedding songs</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Сека"/><biblScope>127</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>æncad ū, aǧ˳ysty farn ma rox kæn</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>тише, не забывай о %sфарне%s дома</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>hush, don't forget about the %sfarn%s at home</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Брит."/><biblScope>34</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Восходит к <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
                        <w>*hvarnah-</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (от %ihvar-%i
                            ‘солнце’)</note></mentioned>: <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>farr</w>
                        <gloss><q>блеск</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>великолепие</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>пышность</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>*farn(frn, prn)</w>
                        <gloss><q>слава</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>знамение</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"
                            ><w>*farnbērtāk</w>
                        <gloss><q>носитель фарна</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"
                            ><w>farnxwantak</w>
                        <gloss><q>наделенный фарном</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="sog"><w>*dīni-farn</w>
                        <gloss><q>фарн религии</q></gloss></mentioned> (ср. ос. <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_dīn"/>%ii farn%i), <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>*βaγīfarn</w>
                        <gloss><q>божий фарн</q></gloss></mentioned> (ср. ос. <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_xucaw"/>%ii farn%i) и др. (<bibl><biblScope xml:lang="ru">I.
                            Gerschevitch. Sogdian Compounds. Trans. Philol. Soc. 1945, стр.
                            139</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">I. Gerschevitch. Sogdian
                            Compounds. Trans. Philol. Soc. 1945, p. 139</biblScope></bibl>),
                        <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/>
                        <w>phārra(-farra)</w>
                        <gloss><q>звание</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>достоинство</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_NTS"/><biblScope>XV 15, 25, 114</biblScope></bibl>),
                        <mentioned xml:lang="xln"><lang/>
                        <w>φαρν</w></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
                            /><biblScope>258</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="xsc"><lang/>
                        <w>φαρν-, farn-</w></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
                            /><biblScope>163–164, 195–196</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned
                        xml:lang="peo"><lang/>
                        <w>farna-</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (в собственных именах, как
                            %iVi(n)dafarnah-%i и др.)</note></mentioned>,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>hvarənah-</w>
                        <gloss><q>слава</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>величие</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>сияние</q></gloss></mentioned>. Обильно представлено в иранских
                    собственных именах, в частности скифо-сарматских: <mentioned xml:lang="xsc"><lang/>
                        <w>Φαρνης, Φαρνακης, Φαρναγος, Φαρνογος, Φαρνοξαρθος, Χοφαρνος, Σαιταφαρνης,
                            ʽΟυαταφαρνης</w></mentioned> и др. В осетинском существует фамильное имя
                    %iFærniatæ%i („Фарниевы“), а в нартовском эпосе один из главных героев зовется
                    %iBuræ-færnyg%i | %iBoræ-færnug%i, т. е. „Бора наделенный фарном“. Cp. также
                        <ref type="xr" target="#entry_Bonværnon"/> (из %iBon-farnon%i) ‘планета
                    Венера’, буквально „(вестница) дневного фарна“. Семантическая связь с ‘солнцем’
                    ясно выступает в охотничьем языке, где %ifærnæ%i д. значит ‘солнце’. Начальный
                    %if%i из %ihv%i не характерен для восточноиранских языков, в частности для
                    осетинского (должно было быть %ixw%i, %ix%i, как в <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_xūr"/> ‘солнце’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_xor"/> |
                    %ixwar%i ‘хлеб в зерне’ и др.; ср., однако, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fyn"/>
                    сон’ из %ihvafna-%i). Считают, что %ifarnah-%i мидийская форма,
                    распространившаяся (через персидское посредство) по всему иранскому миру.
                            (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Gramm._sogd."/><biblScope>I 134, II
                            154</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_BSL"
                            /><biblScope>XXXI %i2%i 72–76</biblScope></bibl>).%n<bibl><ref
                            type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 86, III
                            81</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
                            /><biblScope>40, 43, 71, 83, 163–164, 258</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">Traces back to <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
                        <w>*hvarnah-</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (from %ihvar-%i
                            ‘sun’)</note></mentioned>: <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>farr</w>
                        <gloss><q>shine</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>magnificence</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>splendour</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>*farn(frn, prn)</w>
                        <gloss><q>fame</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>sign</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"
                            ><w>*farnbērtāk</w>
                        <gloss><q>farn bearer</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"
                            ><w>farnxwantak</w>
                        <gloss><q>provided with farn</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="sog"><w>*dīni-farn</w>
                        <gloss><q>farn of the religion</q></gloss></mentioned> (cf. Ossetic <ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_dīn"/>%ii farn%i), <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>*βaγīfarn</w>
                        <gloss><q>God's farn</q></gloss></mentioned> (cf. Ossetic <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_xucaw"/>%ii farn%i) etc. (<bibl><author>I.
                            Gerschevitch.</author><biblScope xml:lang="ru">I. Gerschevitch. Sogdian
                            Compounds. Trans. Philol. Soc. 1945, стр. 139</biblScope><biblScope
                            xml:lang="en">Sogdian Compounds. Trans. Philol. Soc. 1945, p.
                            139</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/>
                        <w>phārra(-farra)</w>
                        <gloss><q>rank</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>dignity</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_NTS"/><biblScope>XV 15, 25, 114</biblScope></bibl>),
                        <mentioned xml:lang="xln"><lang/>
                        <w>φαρν</w></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
                            /><biblScope>258</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="xsc"><lang/>
                        <w>φαρν-, farn-</w></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
                            /><biblScope>163–164, 195–196</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned
                        xml:lang="peo"><lang/>
                        <w>farna-</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (in
                            proper names, as in %iVi(n)dafarnah-%i etc.)</note></mentioned>,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>hvarənah-</w>
                        <gloss><q>fame</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>greatness</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>shine</q></gloss></mentioned>. It is abundantly represented in
                    Iranian proper names, in particular in Scythian-Sarmatian: <mentioned
                        xml:lang="xsc"><lang/>
                        <w>Φαρνης, Φαρνακης, Φαρναγος, Φαρνογος, Φαρνοξαρθος, Χοφαρνος, Σαιταφαρνης,
                            ʽΟυαταφαρνης</w></mentioned> etc. In Ossetic there is a family name
                    %iFærniatæ%i (‘The Farnievs’), and in the Nart epos one of the main characters
                    is called %iBuræ-færnyg%i | %iBoræ-færnug%i, i. e. ‘Bora who is provided with
                    farn’. Cf. also <ref type="xr" target="#entry_Bonværnon"/> (from %iBon-farnon%i)
                    ‘Venus’, literally ‘(ambassadress) of the farn of the day’. The semantic
                    relation to ‘sun’ is clearly seen in hunters' language, where Digor %ifærnæ%i
                    means ‘sun’. The initial %if%i from %ihv%i is not typical of East Iranian
                    languages, particularly, for Ossetic (there should have been %ixw%i, %ix%i, as
                    in <ref type="xr" target="#entry_xūr"/> ‘sun’, <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_xor"/> | %ixwar%i ‘grain bread’ etc.; however, cf. <ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_fyn"/> ‘dream’ from %ihvafna-%i). It is considered
                    that %ifarnah-%i is a Median form, which spread (via Persian) throughout the
                    Iranian world. (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Gramm._sogd."/><biblScope>I
                            134, II 154</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_BSL"/><biblScope>XXXI %i2%i
                            72–76</biblScope></bibl>).%n<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 86, III
                        81</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
                            /><biblScope>40, 43, 71, 83, 163–164, 258</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
                <note type="internal">мб ссылки/примеры в этимологии еще нужны? + очень сомнительный
                    перевод всего</note>
            </entry>
